"""Embedded base64 art for the custom dragon-forged buttons.

This exists so the button art can NEVER go missing on an update again: it
used to be separate PNG files fetched as GitHub OPTIONAL_FILES, but that
meant the art only appeared if it had ALSO been pushed to the repo and
separately fetched -- an easy step to miss. Embedding the bytes directly in
a REQUIRED python module means: the moment basilisk_btn_art.py is present (which
it always will be, same as basilisk_core.py etc.), the art is present. No
separate sync step, no silent optional-file failure.

basilisk.py still checks for an on-disk basilisk-btn-<name>.png FIRST, so you can
still drop in a replacement file later to re-theme a button without
touching this file -- this is only the guaranteed fallback.
"""

